r quality had improved over the previous week, reviving hopes that it might be able to host swimming events for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 279, \"to\": 495, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"regional authorities\", \"from\": 298, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"data\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 328}, {\"ngram\": \"the river's water quality\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous week\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"hopes\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 431}, {\"ngram\": \"swimming events\", \"from\": 462, \"to\": 477}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Joel Stratte McClure, who turns 76 this month, last swam in the Seine for a magazine cover shoot in 1976.\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\", \"score\": 0.9999999994736299, \"rank\": 5.263677574299601e-10, \"text\": \"McClure\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\"}, {\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999297197089, \"rank\": 6.919457901533642e-08, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"last swam\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"a magazine cover shoot\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 593}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite his admiration for the cleanup efforts, McClure expressed concerns about the river's safety.\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 703, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 651, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\", \"score\": 0.9999999994736299, \"rank\": 5.263677574299601e-10, \"text\": \"McClure\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_A._McClure\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his admiration\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 625}, {\"ngram\": \"the cleanup efforts\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 649}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 669, \"to\": 677}, {\"ngram\": \"the river's safety\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 702}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I may regret having swam,\\\" McClure said before entering the water.\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"swam\", \"from\": 726, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"McClure\", \"from\": 733, \"to\": 740}, {\"ngram\": \"the water\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 771}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But if I come back alive, it will prove that the French have done a good job cleaning up the river.\\\"\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 823, \"end\": 829, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8732286096373791, \"rank\": 0.1207888154694011, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good job\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 872}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo first announced her intention to swim in the Seine last month to demonstrate the river's cleanliness, a number of her detractors threatened to urinate in the river on the day she was supposed to swim.\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 1106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 881, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\":